@kinesias Actually, yes, it is related. That's the exact error we'd expect in that situation. Any mounted volume that has a space in it will cause this crash.

You can disable the compaction daemon to fix this for now:

https://github.com/apache/couchdb/issues/802#issuecomment-332590111

@kinesias The issue *is* fixed, on 11 Sep. There just hasn't been a CouchDB release yet that includes this fix.

I gave you a workaround for now in the other ticket you commented on.

Spamming our issue tracker actually makes the release process take longer. Please be patient.

@tonysun83 OK, here's a run I don't need to re-run to merge a PR.

https://travis-ci.org/apache/couchdb/jobs/293295681

Go nuts ;)
